# 8. Sort Dictionary by Value

## Problem

Sort dictionary according to values.

### Example

```python
d = {'a':3,'b':1,'c':2}
```

## Built-in Solution

```python
d = {'a':3,'b':1,'c':2}

result = dict(sorted(d.items(), key=lambda x:x[1]))

print(result)
```

### Output

```python
{'b':1,'c':2,'a':3}
```

## Pure Logic Solution

```python
d = {'a':3,'b':1,'c':2}

keys = list(d.keys())

for i in range(len(keys)):

    for j in range(i+1,len(keys)):

        if d[keys[i]] > d[keys[j]]:

            keys[i], keys[j] = keys[j], keys[i]

for key in keys:
    print(key, d[key])
```


